In a blinding blur, Zak was stood before them, his whirling blades throwing crackling energy into the bulkheads of the ship whenever they met each other or a bullet. The assassins slowly backed off as they saw the spatters of molten metal that were once armour-piercing rifle rounds land at his feet. He leaped forwards, his shorter blade seeking the throat of the lead assassin, his longer sword driving the other two together with a series of flickering feints. As the first corpse dropped to the ground, he finished the other two off with a deceptively slow slash that dropped to waist height as his wakizashi met the skull of the final remaining thug. Lifting his face skywards, he let out a long howl and shuddered as the adrenaline boosters over his adrenal glands quadrupled his power, his face flushing as the oxygen gland located in his throat increased the oxygen supply of his blood. With barely even a look backwards, the psychotic swordsman dashed off, his weapons thirsty for the blood of more victims. <p>'It's better to light a candle than curse the darkness, and better than both to remain unseen.'- NeoAngel. .................

