Decker opened the armor storage closet and began tossing Assault shields to his men.  He took one up himself and slowly began marching down the passageway and out the hatch, firing at anyone who got close from behind the safety of his shield.  <br>
<br>
The rest of the men followed suit, marching in rows of four out the door and into the heart of the battle.  The ranks of assasins began gradually dissipating, and they began to retreat.<br>
<br>
Soon the area was clear, leaving the men to awe at the destruction of their ship, and wonder what wasteland Caron had dropped them on.<br>
<br>
&quot;Alright, everyone...listen up!&quot; The chief gathered his men's attention.  Caron watched from just inside the ship, leaning against the hull with her arms crossed.  <br>
<br>
&quot;As this was our first battle,&quot; he continued, &quot;I'll now apoint my commanding officers.  Caron, as you all know will be my advisor and second in command.&quot; A few disgruntled sighs went up from around the group.  &quot;Don't worry, I'll teach her to use her weapon before our next encounter with the enemy.&quot;<br>
<br>
A tired laugh came from his left side, &quot;You'd better, I may not be able to block those bullets next time!&quot;  Zak bent down, resting his hands on his knees.<br>
<br>
