Suddenly the blacc-clad individuals turns around, breathing a sigh of releif Alec continues his journey back to the ship occasionally looking over his shoulder to check that he has lost the tail completely.  As he approaches the ship Alec holsters his weapon and removes his helmet revealing his battle-scarred face, ascending the ramp he hesitates for a moment but the continues, as he steps inside the ship he says &quot;excuse me I've come to offer my services, who's in charge here&quot;. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=neoangel>NeoAngel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/20/02 10:51 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:Angel+ByTheGun RPG</span><hr size=1> Zak pressed the attack, driving D'Archon backwards into the wall of the Terran Embassy. But D'Archon's shadowblade weaved an impenetrable wall of darkness around him, backed by his considerable psionic shielding.<br>
'So, mighty warrior' he spoke as his blade whirled a complete circle around him, leaving his hand, cleaving through the steel wall behind him and just missing Zak before returning to his gauntleted fist. 'You still possess the blade of our master? The twin to the blade in my fist? You were a fool to leave it behind, and a fool not to disguise your sending just now. I sensed it, and intercepted it. Your martian freak friend will not be able to aid you!'<br>
'If there's one thing I learned in the fighting pits you condemned me to after our masters death' Zak retorted, 'It's that the light in the blade is the light in the heart!'<br>
His twinned blades once more crackled with energy. His torn jacket revealed a metallic implant in his spine as he spun around, a syringe embedded under his skin. As his blades crossed in the air, it hissed and injected a fluid of his own devising into his spinal cord. As his eyes began to glow with a harsh red light, his muscles bulged as the physical enhancer took affect. He grew to match D'Archons height and bulk, and his motions became more fluid.<br>
'The neural interface enhancer! They destroyed the test samples!' D'Archon gasped through his mask. 'How did you procure one?'<br>
'That's an easy one. I was one of the test samples. They removed my long-term memory, and put me in the fighting pits. But I survived. All my memory is encrypted in the hilts of these blades!' Zak cried as his swords pierced D'Archon's body, one through his throat, one effortlessly batting aside his great sword and plunging into his left eye. Zak released the hilts and collapsed to the ground, his body returning to normal as he began to spasm and blood trickled out of his nose and mouth. <p>'It's better to light a candle than curse the darkness, and better than both to remain unseen.'- NeoAngel. .................

